56    /**
57    * <p>JSDoc information describing JavaScript code. JSDoc is represented as a
58    * unified object with fields for each JSDoc annotation, even though some
59    * combinations are incorrect. For instance, if a JSDoc describes an enum,
60    * it cannot have information about a return type. This implementation
61    * takes advantage of such incompatibilities to reuse fields for multiple
62    * purposes, reducing memory consumption.</p>
63    *
64    * <p>Constructing {@link JSDocInfo} objects is simplified by
65    * {@link JSDocInfoBuilder} which provides early incompatibility detection.</p>
66    *
67    */

301    private static final int MASK_PRESERVETRY = 0x00000010; // @preserveTry
302    private static final int MASK_NOCHECK = 0x00000020; // @notypecheck
303    private static final int MASK_OVERRIDE = 0x00000040; // @override
304    private static final int MASK_NOALIAS = 0x00000080; // @noalias
305    private static final int MASK_DEPRECATED = 0x00000100; // @deprecated
306    private static final int MASK_INTERFACE = 0x00000200; // @interface
307    private static final int MASK_EXPORT = 0x00000400; // @export
308    private static final int MASK_NOSHADOW = 0x00000800; // @noshadow
309    private static final int MASK_FILEOVERVIEW = 0x00001000; // @fileoverview
310    private static final int MASK_IMPLICITCAST = 0x00002000; // @implicitCast
311    private static final int MASK_NOSIDEEFFECTS = 0x00004000; // @nosideeffects
312    private static final int MASK_EXTERNS = 0x00008000; // @externs
